      <section eId="sec_CCRP-657-1">
        <num>CCRP 657.1</num>
        <heading>657.1.  Conditional release; criteria</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-657-1__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>At any time the court considers a recommendation from the hospital-based review
panel that the person may be discharged or released on probation, it may place the insanity
acquittee on conditional release if it finds the following:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CCRP-657-1__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Based on the factors which the court shall consider pursuant to Article 657, he
does not need inpatient hospitalization but needs outpatient treatment, supervision, and
monitoring to prevent his condition from deteriorating to a degree that he would likely
become dangerous to self and others.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCRP-657-1__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Appropriate outpatient treatment, supervision, and monitoring  are reasonably
available.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCRP-657-1__subsec_A__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>There is significant reason to believe that the insanity acquittee, if conditionally
released, would comply with the conditions specified.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCRP-657-1__subsec_A__subsec_4">
            <num>(4)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Conditional release will not present an undue risk of danger to others or self, as
defined in R.S. 28:2.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-657-1__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court shall subject a conditionally released insanity acquittee to such orders
and conditions it deems will best meet the acquittee's need for treatment, supervision, and
monitoring and will  best serve the interests of justice and society.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-657-1__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>These provisions for conditional release may also be applied to discharges of
pretrial defendants found unrestorably incompetent to proceed pursuant to Article 648(B).</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112681</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
